2020 has been a year like no other. Joy came in small doses and even small cups of coffee. Decaf coffee with a bit of eggnog, a touch of vanilla and a dash of nutmeg has been my seasonal treat for years. Because the Starbucks in my area no longer brew decaf  the only option is an Americano. The result is a cup of coffee at nearly $5. Yes, the price increased in a year of the pandemic. Wow!

I said that’s exactly what I want but whenever I go to Starbucks I ask for an espresso macchiato wet and my barista knows what I mean.  Then because I get to have exactly what I want I usually tip more than my drink.  I went to an Italian restaurant and I was informed that what I really wanted was a Cortado. I went on a wednesday morning at 8:40am and immediately noticed how well functioning and lively this Starbucks was that day. This location had all the typical menu options, a large 7 foot air wall with usual refrigerated products and some bakery options mainly scones and muffins (I believe).  I ordered a tall whole milk latte, and waited maybe 3-4 minutes. There was 5 people working that day, most were preoccupied with a few large orders. Since I was in a rush that day, I noticed I could've saved time by ordering in advance, as there seemed to be a quick turnaround on online orders.  All in all, this was a decent location. You can expect excellent fast service, at least from my perspective.

My son and I are from Wisconsin but traveled to Chicago for a meeting. We were a bit early so we decided to stop at a near by Starbucks. Not only was the staff very friendly but we were pleasantly surprised to see board games available to play. My son and I truly enjoyed playing connect four while also enjoying our delicious drinks. The manager was so sweet and nice as well. She stopped over to talk with us and was happy to see us enjoying the games. I wish we lived closer so we could visit that Starbucks more often. However, whenever we are that area of Chicago we will definitely be stopping by!
